00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.029
What Is a T-47 and Why Do I Need One?

00:00:02.912 --> 00:00:06.422
If you plan to use an existing survey
when selling your home, you will

00:00:06.422 --> 00:00:10.762
be required to complete a document
called a T-47, also known as the

00:00:10.762 --> 00:00:12.692
Residential Real Property Affidavit.

00:00:13.962 --> 00:00:17.832
The T-47 is used when the buyer and
title company rely on an existing

00:00:17.832 --> 00:00:19.772
survey instead of ordering a new one.

00:00:20.532 --> 00:00:23.322
This form allows you, as the
seller, to confirm that the

00:00:23.322 --> 00:00:25.332
survey on file is still accurate.

00:00:26.775 --> 00:00:31.525
The T-47 works together with the survey
to help the title company determine what

00:00:31.525 --> 00:00:33.805
title insurance coverage they can provide.

00:00:34.275 --> 00:00:39.474
If a T-47 is not completed, the title
company may require a new survey, which

00:00:39.474 --> 00:00:41.844
can add cost and delay to the transaction.

00:00:43.025 --> 00:00:47.474
One of the most important sections of
the T-47 asks for the date of the survey.

00:00:47.985 --> 00:00:51.804
This should be the date of the most
recent survey of the property, whether it

00:00:51.804 --> 00:00:54.035
was ordered by you or a previous owner.

00:00:55.405 --> 00:01:00.014
Using a different date often results in
the title company requesting a new survey.

00:01:00.724 --> 00:01:04.094
The form also asks you to confirm
whether any major changes have occurred

00:01:04.094 --> 00:01:05.975
to the property since that survey date.

00:01:06.505 --> 00:01:10.424
This includes things like new
structures, additions, changes to

00:01:10.424 --> 00:01:12.304
boundary fences, or new easements.

00:01:13.124 --> 00:01:16.115
If there have been no changes,
you can simply write “None.”

00:01:17.937 --> 00:01:22.287
The T-47 is an affidavit, which means
it must be signed in front of a notary.

00:01:22.897 --> 00:01:24.417
Do not sign it ahead of time.

00:01:24.837 --> 00:01:27.767
You will need to sign the form
while the notary is present.

00:01:28.667 --> 00:01:33.127
In short, the T-47 helps avoid the
cost and delay of a new survey,

00:01:33.317 --> 00:01:36.617
but only if it is completed
accurately and properly notarized.

